verbose_text: As shown in Fig. XREF_FIG a, treatment of SW480 cells with increasing concentrations of maoecrystal I for 24 h reduced expressions of c-myc, cyclin D1, survivin, and Axin2 in a dose dependent manner, which showed that the inhibition of cancer cell growth is associated with Wnt signaling inhibition by maoecrystal I. Regulation of beta-catenin level is a feature of Wnt signaling pathway.
